          Checklist for Guile-Termios Releases
        ========================================

 1. Update version tag in:

    - doc/guile-termios.mdwn: Strip the +git tag and increment.

    - scheme/termios.scm: Which version does the manual refer to?

 2. Update CHANGES with all user-visible changes that are not yet listed.

 3. Add (released ...) tag to the most recent version.

 4. Commit those changes.

 5. Tag that commit.

 6. Generate reference documentation and update the ‘manual’ branch with
    the resulting files.

 7. Commit updated files to ‘manual’ branch.

 8. Tag the latest commit in the ‘manual’ branch.

 9. Push changes and tags to the public repository.

10. Add +git tag to ‘termios-version’ in “scheme/termios.scm”.
